      <section id="varieties" class="sec-padding">
        <h3 class="section-heading">VARIETIES</h3>
        <div class="sec-content-div flexible">
          <div class="tile">
            <img src="https://www.bakepedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/grapes_1-copy.jpg" alt="photo of concord grapes" />
            <h4>Concord</h4>
            <p>
              The Concord grape is a cultivar derived from the grape species Vitis labrusca that are used as table grapes, wine grapes and juice grapes.They are often used to make grape juice,grape-flavored soft drinks, and candy.             </p>
          </div>
          <div class="tile">
            <img src="https://www.mashed.com/img/gallery/what-are-cotton-candy-grapes-and-what-do-they-taste-like-upgrade/intro-1678298061.jpg"alt="photo of cotton candy grapes" />
            <h4>Cotton Candy</h4>
            <p>
              Cotton Candy is a trademark for a variety of sweet white table grapes of the cultivar IFG Seven whose flavour has been compared to cotton candy.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="tile">
            <img src="https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQy9icUlsH1htY670qgCmlUKdvG0rY25jq_V8wYpzDeNw&s" alt="photo of Crimson grapes" />
            <h4>Crimson</h4>
            <p>
              Ruby-coloured Fresho Crimson grapes are uniquely large,round,and best quality grapes.They have a crunchy skin, fleshy pulp in colour.Seedless Crimson Grapes boasts a crisp-juicy texture and an excellent, sweet flavour.       </p>
          </div>
          <div class="tile">
            <img src="https://i5.walmartimages.ca/images/Thumbnails/616/557/6000199616557.jpg" alt="photo of Black Monukka grapes" />
            <h4>Black Monukka</h4>
            <p>
              The Black Monukka grape is a hardy,seedless European variety.It is thought to have originated from a Persian grape'Munaqqa',which translate to raisin.Its fruit is large oval shape,sweet and crisp. 
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="tile">
            <img src="https://frugivore-storage.s3.amazonaws.com/media/package/img_one/2021-04-23/Red_Globe_kraken.jpg" alt="photo of red globe grapes" />
            <h4>Red Globe</h4>
            <p>
             The Red Globe is a variety of very large,seeded red grapes with firm flesh used mainly as a table grape.It can be grown outdoors in very warm areas with long growing seasons such as California.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="tile">
            <img src="https://buenazo.cronosmedia.glr.pe/original/2020/12/18/5fdd0cda63b4a8490d7e3c9e.jpg" alt="photo of Sultana grapes" />
            <h4>Sultana</h4>
            <p>
             The sultana is a "white", oval seedless grape variety also called the sultanina,Lady de Coverly, and oval-fruited Kishmish. It is also known as İzmir üzümü in Turkey since this variety has been extensively grown in the region around İzmir.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
